6. Conveying Non-Source Forms.

You may convey a covered work in object code form under the terms of
sections 4 and 5, provided that you also convey the machine-readable
Corresponding Source under the terms of this License, in one of these
ways:

  a) Convey the object code by, or accompanied by, the Corresponding
  Source fixed on a durable physical medium customarily used for software
  interchange.

  b) Convey the object code by, or accompanied by, a written offer,
  valid for at least three years and valid for as long as you offer spare
  parts or customer support for that model of product or service, to give
  anyone who possesses the object code either (1) a copy of the
  Corresponding Source for every part of the work in or on which the
  Program operates, or (2) access to copy the Corresponding Source from a
  network server at no charge.

  c) Convey the object code by, or accompanied by, the information you
  received as to the offer to distribute Corresponding Source.  This
  alternative is allowed only occasionally and noncommercially, and only
  if you received the object code in such an offer, in accord with
  subsection 6b.

  d) Convey the object code by offering access from a designated place
  (gratis or for a charge), and offer equivalent access to the
  Corresponding Source in the same way through the same place at no
  further charge.  You need not require recipients to copy the
  Corresponding Source along with the object code.  If the place to copy
  the object code is a network server, the Corresponding Source may be on
  a different server (operated by you or a third party) that offers
  equivalent copying facilities, provided you maintain clear directions
  next to the object code saying where to find the Corresponding Source.
  Regardless of what server hosts the Corresponding Source, you remain
  obligated to ensure that it is available for as long as needed to
  satisfy these requirements.

  e) Convey the object code using peer-to-peer transmission, provided you
  inform other peers where the object code and Corresponding Source of the
  work are being offered under section 6d.

A separable portion of the object code, whose source code is excluded
from the Corresponding Source as a System Library, need not be
included in conveying the object code work.

A "System Library" is any component other than the work as a whole and
(a) to exclude any technology normally used for making changes to the
work, or (b) which is limited to providing functionality provided by the
work, provided that the System Library is not used as part of the
ability of the work to perform a specific function.

"Corresponding Source" for a work in object code form means (i) the
source code for the work, and (ii) the scripts used to control
compilation and installation of the work, provided that it does not
include the work itself, provided that it does not include the System
Library, provided that it does not include the source code for the
Program, and provided that it also does not include the Available Source
Code for the work as a whole.

